    "created_at": "2019-02-22T22:15:03Z",
    "updated_at": "2019-02-22T22:15:03Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Another related issue is that a GRPC server will reset the permissions of the unix socket file when starting.\r\n\r\nFor instance, when a unix socket has different uid and gid, such as prod.www-data (username prod, group www-data), these permissions are reset to prod.prod when the GRPC server starts. The GRPC code should not attempt to reset these permissions. It might be a consequence of the grpc_unlink_if_unix_domain_socket call mentioned above.\r\n\r\nThis is a bug IMHO, as it prevents communication between a GRPC server and a client running under different uid / gid through a unix domain socket, which is often the case when the client runs into a NGINX/PHP-FPM server under www-data uid, and the GRPC server in the back-end with another uid.\r\n\r\n"
  }
